Let \(\epsilon_{n}^{t}\) be the Gaussian noise added in the diffusion step \(n\) during the forward process of the diffusion model and \(x_{0}^{t}\) be the original value in the time series. The perturbed signal at diffusion step \(n\) can be expressed as: \(x_{n}^{t}=x_{n-1}^{t}+\epsilon_{n}^{t}\). Let \(\sigma_{n}^{2}\) and \(\sigma_{\epsilon_{n}}^{2}\) be the variances of perturbed time series and noise respectively at diffusion step \(n\) while \(\sigma_{n-1}^{2}\) is the variance of the time series at diffusion step \(n-1\)

