since \(\exp(-\alpha_{n}|0|^{\beta_{n}})=\exp(0)=1\). Therefore, as \(k\to 0\), \(\mathcal{S}_{n}^{f}(\omega_{k})=|f_{n}^{k}|^{2}\) approaches the variance \(\sigma_{n}^{2}\). So, we can write:

